Under the optimum time, the sensing performance of this platform with various activities of HAase (0–50.0 U/mL) is shown in Fig. 5
                        A. With the increase of HAase activity, the fluorescence intensities of PVP-CuNCs at 430 nm decreased slightly while those of DAP at 560 nm increase. Furthermore, a good linear relationship is found between the ratio of fluorescence intensity at 560 nm to that at 430 nm (F560/F430) and HAase activity in the range of 0–10.0 U/mL (Fig. 5B). The linear regression equation can be described as Y = 0.0258X+0.281 (R2 = 0.995). The limit of detection (LOD) was calculated as 0.43 U/mL (S/N = 3). The performance of the proposed sensing platform is compared with the previous work (Table 1
                        ), this strategy presents its competitiveness in sensitivity, which attributes to the combination of controlled release and mimic activity enhanced Fe–N–C nanozymes in the sensing system.
